      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2021-07-15 02:12:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nOne thing we've talked about recently is to split conf-sanity into several parts (LU-14772):\n- subtests that do \"reformat; something; cleanup; reformat\"\n- subtests that only do \"setup; something on existing config; cleanup\"\nThese are intermixed in conf-sanity today, and are relatively sensitive to changes in ordering, etc.\n- upgrade tests from previous versions\n\nThere are three main reasons for splitting up the tests:\n- shorten the duration of conf-sanity so that it can run in parallel in 1/3 or 1/4 of the wall-clock time\n- remove the second \"reformat to default\" in the subtests, which is a waste of time if the next test does another reformat itself\n- avoid unnecessary \"cleanup; setup\" if the subtests are using the same configuration and do not need this\n\nThat might be a useful precursor to adding in a set of subtests that require a separate MGS to run, so they can do this at the beginning",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
